  "jd_text": "2026 Asset Wealth Management Machine Learning Engineer-Summer Associate\r\nJersey City, NJ, United States\r\nApply Now\r\n\r\n0%\r\nResume Match\r\n0 of 6 keywords\r\nSimplify\r\nSimplify\r\nV1\r\nV2\r\nJob Identification\r\n210687370\r\nJob Category\r\nSeasonal Employee\r\nBusiness Unit\r\nAsset & Wealth Management\r\nPosting Date\r\n04/01/2026, 05:00 PM\r\nLocations\r\n 575 Washington Blvd, Jersey City, NJ, 07310, US\r\nJob Schedule\r\nFull time\r\nBase Pay/Salary\r\nJersey City,NJ $135,000.00-$155,000.00\r\nJob Description\r\nJoin our team as an ML Engineer Intern to help reimagine Private Banking by developing advanced AI agents and impactful machine learning solutions. Collaborate across business lines to research, build, and deploy innovative agents. Make a real impact by transforming client experiences with the latest AI technologies.\r\n\r\nAs an Asset Wealth Management Machine Learning Engineer - Summer Associate, you will apply advanced NLP, LLM, and AI techniques to generate actionable insights from large-scale financial data. Work with industry experts to design scalable data pipelines and support data-driven investment decisions. Empower automation and innovation on our cutting-edge investment platform.\r\n\r\nJob responsibilities\r\n\r\nDesign, deploy and manage prompt-based models on LLMs for various NLP tasks in the financial services domain\r\nConduct research on prompt engineering techniques to improve the performance of prompt-based models within the financial services field, exploring and utilizing LLM orchestration and agentic AI libraries.\r\nBuild comprehensive testing setups to evaluate model performance and ensure efficacy and reliability.\r\nCollaborate with engineering teams to deliver high-quality, scalable solutions.\r\nStudy scientific articles and research papers to identify emerging techniques and discover new approaches.\r\nRequired qualifications, capabilities, and skills\r\n\r\nAdvanced degree in Data Science, Computer Science, or Machine Learning.\r\nProven experience in natural language processing and working with large language models.\r\nProficiency in programming languages such as Python and familiarity with machine learning libraries and frameworks.\r\nExcellent communication skills and ability to work collaboratively in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.\r\nStrong analytical skills with an understanding of financial markets and asset management.",
  "cover_letter": {
    "tex": "% HIREX base_coverletter.tex (anchor-based, token-ready)\n\\documentclass[11pt]{article}\n\\usepackage[margin=1in]{geometry}\n\\usepackage[hidelinks]{hyperref}\n\\pagenumbering{gobble}\n\\setlength{\\parskip}{0.65em}\n\\begin{document}\n\n\\noindent Date: April 02, 2026\n\n\\vspace{10pt}\nHiring Manager \\\\\ncompany name \\\\\n\n\\vspace{10pt}\nDear Hiring Manager,\n\nYour organization's Asset and Wealth Management team is especially attractive to me because I'd really like to have the opportunity to use advanced AI technologies to help rethink the Private Banking client experience. I'm in a position to positively impact client experiences through machine learning because of my background in AI and data analysis. In my previous role at JPMorgan Chase, for instance, I created machine learning algorithms that helped improve the efficiency of a process by at least thirty percent. I also developed a predictive modelling tool that improved the accuracy of forecasts by twenty-five percent, which ultimately resulted in better outcomes for investment strategies of clients. In addition to my technical skills, I have experience with large language models and am proficient in Python, which prepares me to address many of the unique challenges of this position. I am focused on designing and implementing advanced prompt-based models to improve the effectiveness and scalability of NLP tasks and will spend time collaborating with engineering teams on how to best refine these solutions. In my opinion, teamwork is one of the most important keys to success for any innovative project. I'm excited about the prospect of how my background can be leveraged to build out an investment platform at your company. I anticipate contributing to enhancing client usage of your services and improving innovation through my knowledge of machine learning and data analysis.\n\nSincerely, \\\\\nSri Akash Kadali \\\\\nkadali18@umd.edu \\\\\n+1 240-726-9356\n\n\\end{document}",
